   "source": [
    "<div style='background:#4a4a4a;color:white;padding:14px 22px;border-radius:6px;font-size:20px;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "2 &middot; Comprehensive Training Infrastructure & Regularization\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style='padding:16px 6px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:#000;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Augmentation Pipeline:** Applied Random Rotation ($\pm 15^\circ$), Sharpness adjustments, Color jittering, and Random Perspective transforms to simulate real-world environmental distortion.\n",
    "- **Advanced Regularization Techniques Implemented:**\n",
    "  - **Label Smoothing (0.1):** Hard targets (0 or 1) force models to over-fit. Smoothing regularizes the logit space by assigning a tiny penalty probability to other classes.\n",
    "  - **Cosine Annealing Learning Rate Schedule:** Continuously scales down the learning rate following a cosine curve to smoothly guide weights into narrow, global minima.\n",
    "  - **Automatic Mixed Precision (AMP - FP16):** Leverages NVIDIA Tensor Cores to speed up training while cutting GPU VRAM consumption in half.\n",
    "  - **Gradient Clipping (max_norm=1.0):** Clamps backpropagated gradients to eliminate the threat of Exploding Gradients during heavy structural updates.\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div style='background:#4a4a4a;color:white;padding:14px 22px;border-radius:6px;font-size:20px;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "3 &middot; Model 1: Custom Deep CNN Architecture & Design Choices\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style='padding:16px 6px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:#000;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Architectural Choice:** Built 3 specialized Convolutional Blocks using dual $3\\times3$ convolutions per block to steadily increase the model's receptive field before downsampling.\n",
    "- **Advanced Engineering Adjustments:**\n",
    "  - <span style='color:#c0392b;'>**`bias=False` Implementation:**</span> Removed all bias parameters preceding `BatchNorm2d` and `BatchNorm1d` layers to mathematically prevent parameter redundancy.\n",
    "  - <span style='color:#c0392b;'>**`Dropout2d` Integration:**</span> Swapped standard Dropout for Spatial 2D Dropout within the convolutional feature maps. This drops entire channels, eliminating spatial co-adaptation.\n",
    "  - **Global Average Pooling (GAP):** Collapses spatial feature matrices ($H \\times W$) directly down to $1 \\times 1$. This drastically drops the dense layer bottleneck parameter requirements.\n",
    "  - **Explicit Kaiming (He) Initialization:** Isolated routine executing stable variance initialization specifically calibrated for ReLU active networks.\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "\n",
    "class TrafficSignCNN(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, num_classes=43):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "\n",
    "        # High-End Engineering: bias=False avoids mathematical redundancy before BatchNorm layers\n",
    "        def conv_block(in_ch, out_ch):\n",
    "            return nn.Sequential(\n",
    "                nn.Conv2d(in_ch, out_ch, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False),\n",
    "                nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch),\n",
    "                nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
    "                nn.Conv2d(out_ch, out_ch, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False),\n",
    "                nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch),\n",
    "                nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
    "                nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2),\n",
    "                nn.Dropout2d(p=0.25) # Spatial Dropout to prevent channel co-adaptation\n",
    "            )\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Consolidated Feature Extraction Blocks\n",
    "        self.block1 = conv_block(3, 32)    # Extracts low-level structural edges & color gradients\n",
    "        self.block2 = conv_block(32, 64)   # Extracts intermediate geometric shapes & corners\n",
    "        self.block3 = conv_block(64, 128)  # Extracts high-level class-specific sign signatures\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Global Average Pooling eliminates fully-connected parameter bottlenecks\n",
    "        self.gap = nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Fully Connected Non-Linear Classification Head\n",
    "        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Flatten(),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(128, 256, bias=False),\n",
    "            nn.BatchNorm1d(256),\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
    "            nn.Dropout(p=0.5),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(256, num_classes) # Outputs raw unnormalized Logits\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Explicit Structural Initialization Process\n",
    "        self._init_weights()\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _init_weights(self):\n",
    "        for m in self.modules():\n",
    "            if isinstance(m, nn.Conv2d):\n",
    "                nn.init.kaiming_normal_(m.weight, nonlinearity='relu')\n",
    "            elif isinstance(m, (nn.BatchNorm2d, nn.BatchNorm1d)):\n",
    "                nn.init.ones_(m.weight)\n",
    "                nn.init.zeros_(m.bias)\n",
    "            elif isinstance(m, nn.Linear):\n",
    "                nn.init.kaiming_normal_(m.weight, nonlinearity='relu')\n",
    "                if m.bias is not None:\n",
    "                    nn.init.zeros_(m.bias)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        x = self.block1(x)\n",
    "        x = self.block2(x)\n",
    "        x = self.block3(x)\n",
    "        x = self.gap(x)\n",
    "        return self.classifier(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model instantiation and pipeline validation\n",
    "DEVICE = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\n",
    "NUM_CLASSES = 43\n",
    "IMG_SIZE = 32\n",
    "\n",
    "cnn_model = TrafficSignCNN(NUM_CLASSES).to(DEVICE)\n",
    "total_params = sum(p.numel() for p in cnn_model.parameters())\n",
    "print(f'Custom CNN - Total Trainable Parameters: {total_params:,}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verification test across mock batch dimension tensors\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    dummy_out = cnn_model(torch.zeros(2, 3, IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE).to(DEVICE))\n",
    "print(f'Structural Shape Verification: Output Tensor Shape is {tuple(dummy_out.shape)} -> OK')"
   ]
  },
